#  Initialization

DOCUMENT();

loadMacros(
  "PGstandard.pl",
  "MathObjects.pl",
  "PGML.pl",
  "PGgraphmacros.pl",
  "PGcourse.pl",

);

##############################################

#Percent word problem

Context("LimitedNumeric");
Context()->{format}{number} = "%.1f";

Context()->flags->set(

  tolerance => 0.051,

  tolType => "absolute",

);

$a = random(26,85);
$b = random(101,299);

$ans = $a/100*$b;
$rhs = $a*$b;
$decimal = $a/100;

##############################################

TEXT(beginproblem());

BEGIN_PGML

[$a]% of [$b] is what? (Round your answer to the nearest tenth.)

 [________]{$ans}


END_PGML

##############################################



BEGIN_PGML_SOLUTION
We can set this problem up as a proportion or as an equation.

*Proportion*

[``\frac{\textrm{part}}{\textrm{total}} = \frac{\textrm{percent}}{100}``]

[``\frac{x}{[$b]} = \frac{[$a]}{100}``]

Cross mulitply and solve:

[`100x = [$b] \cdot [$a]`]

[`100x = [$rhs]`]

[`x = [$rhs] \div 100 = [$ans]`]

*Equation*

[`\textrm{percent} \times \textrm{total} = \textrm{part}`]

[`[$decimal] \cdot [$b] = x`]

[`x = [$ans]`]


END_PGML_SOLUTION

ENDDOCUMENT();